Website updates!

RoomHistory objects are created at the same time as SensorReadings. They are a record of previous SensorReadings (plus a room ID), because the next SensorReading coming from the same MAC address will overwrite the older one. The "dummy ping" functionality has been updated to do this "overwrite" functionality in the Cloud Code. (Data coming from a real sensor already does this.)

This commit also includes the first bits of code for selecting a room to send a dummy ping to.

Added "afterSave" function in Cloud Code that will update the RoomSummary for the room that corresponds with the MAC address in each new SensorReading.
Also corrected functionality so the "X" image refers to occupied and "O" refers to not occupied.
